{"word":"κατεύχομαι","slug":"κατεύχομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατεύχομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-εύξομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <i>to pray earnestly</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>κ. τινι</el> <i>to pray</i> to one, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to make a prayer</i> or <i>vow</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in bad sense,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to pray against</i> one, <i>imprecate</i> curses <i>on</i> one, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>imprecari</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; also, <el>κατ. τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to boast that . .</i> , <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}